com.deadmandungeons.audioconnect

Class AudioConnectClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.deadmandungeons.audioconnect.AudioConnectClient

  • public class AudioConnectClient
extends Object
    The class which operates as the data supplier client to an AudioConnect server.
    Note: this class and its operations are thread safe.
    Author:
    Jon

      • connect

        public io.netty.util.concurrent.Future<?> connect()
                                           throws IllegalStateException
        Establish a connection with the configured AudioConnect server.
        If a connection is already established or is currently being established, this will do nothing.
        Returns:
        a Future for when a valid connection has been established with the AudioConnect server
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if called after shutdown()

      • disconnect

        public io.netty.util.concurrent.Future<?> disconnect()
        Disconnect from the AudioConnect server and reset.
        If a connection is not established or being established, this will do nothing.
        Returns:
        a Future for when the connection has been fully disconnected and closed

      • shutdown

        public io.netty.util.concurrent.Future<?> shutdown()
        Disconnect from the AudioConnect server and shutdown this client.
        If this client has already been or is being shutdown, this will do nothing.
        Note: This client instance will no longer be able to connect after this is called.
        Returns:
        a Future for when this client has completely disconnected and been shutdown.
